    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Accurately estimating the seroprevalence of antibodies to SARS-CoV-2 requires the use of appropriate methods. Bayesian statistics provides a natural framework for considering the variabilities of specificity and sensitivity of the antibody tests, as well as for incorporating prior knowledge of viral infection prevalence. We present a full Bayesian approach for this purpose, and we demonstrate the utility of our approach using a recently published large-scale dataset from the U.S. CDC.</jats:p>",
